title: Alabama father and son killed in crash with each other
text: show ad Son was driving home from partying at 4am when he hit his father's bread delivery truck head-on and killed them both Jeffrey Morris Brasher, 50, and Austin Blaine Brasher, 22, were killed in a head-on car collision with each other A relative said Austin was returning from a night of partying when the crash occurred Alabama state troopers said alcohol is a factor in the fatal car crash The father's Ford pickup collided with his son's Chevrolet on Fayette County 49
